               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the owners; name of the protagonist (both Libanos and Mäṭaˤ);&#xD;
elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
Four lines, divided into 2 groups alternating with black lines, in the incipit folio of Text I;&#xD;
incipit (two lines) of Text II; incipit of each miracle in Text II (one-two lines);&#xD;
incipit (two lines) of Text III (fol. 60ra) and some passages; the word sälam.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- For the Texts of Gädlä Libanos, Täʾamrä Libanos and Mälkǝʾa Libanos compare them to the edited version: A. BAUSI, La «Vita» e i «miracoli» di Libānos, Lovanii 2003 (CSCO 595, 596 [SAe 105, 106]).</note>
                     <note>- The colour red, used for rubrications, is more vivid in fols. 62va (l.17) – 63rb.</note>
                     <note>- Miracles 10, 14, 17, 18, 22, 23 are not numbered.</note>
                     <note>- Text II ends with subsriptio (supplication), separated with a chain or black and red dots followed by black and red lines:</note>
                     <note>Fol. 63rb: ለዘጸሐፎ፡ ወለዘአጽሐፎ፨ ለዘአንበቦ፡ ወለዘተርጎሞ፨ ወለዘሰምአ፡ ቃላቲሁ፨ በጸሎቱ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ሊባኖስ፡ ህቡረ፡ ይምሐሮሙ፨ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዝገብረ፡ ተዝካርየ፡ ወዘአብዓለ፡ በዓልየ፡ ወዘጸውአ፡ ስምየ፡ ይድኃን፡ እምኵነኔ፡ ወደይን፡ ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘተሳየጦ፡ በወርቆሙ፨˂…˃ ምስለ፡ ደቂቆሙ፨ ጸሎቱ፡ ወበረከቱ፡ የሃሉ፡ ምስሌነ፡ ለዓለመ፡ አለም፡ አሜን፨</note>
